        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 30 at 6:44PM EDT by NWS Raleigh NC</headline>
        <description>At 643 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Enon, or near East Bend, moving east at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Huntsville, Pfafftown, Stanleyville, Winston-Salem, Walkertown,
Lewisville, Sedge Garden, and Clemmons.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
